  <h1>Isobasin</h1>

<p>This tool can be used to divide a landscape into a group of nearly equal-sized watersheds, known as isobasins. The user must specify the name of a flow pointer (flow direction) raster, a catchment area (flow accumulation) raster, the output raster name, and the isobasin target area. The flow pointer and accumulation rasters should be generated using the <a href="FlowPointerD8.html"><b><i>D8 algorithm</b></i></a>. The isobasin target area must be in the same units as the catchment area image. Notice that a temporary image is created during the execution of this tool and that it is deleted upon completion.</p>

<p><b><i>NoData</i></b> values in the input flow pointer or accumulation rasters are assigned <i><b>NoData</b></i> values in the output image. The output raster is of the <i>float</i> data type and <i>categorical</i> data scale.</p>

